19/04/2006
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The head of the National Anti-corruption Department, Daniel Morar, announced on Tuesday (18 April) that prosecutors are investigating seven parliament members: four from the main opposition Social Democratic Party, two from another opposition formation, the Conservative Party, and one from the Democratic Party (PD) -- the first case of alleged corruption involving the ruling coalition. 
Morar provided few details, but said PD member Stelian Dutu, former chairman of the Constanta County Council, is being investigated for an illegal land purchase in the Neptun resort. 
(Nine o'clock - 19/04/06)
